Template Class By Breath Cue

Intro to class, ask/explain what class entails if students are new

Warm up & Grounding - 5 minutes
Start on back, practing breathing, share grounding statements
IN: Supported Staff Pose
EX: Remain, transition to table top in a way that makes sense
IN: Cat 
EX: Cow

Transition to downdog in a way that makes sense

Flow 1 - 15 minutes
IN: R Leg Up (Dog Split) 
EX: Low Lunge
IN: Low Crescent Lunge 
EX: Pyramid Fold
IN: Low Lunge 
Ex: Rag Doll, Stay for a full breath
IN: Chair Pose 
EX: Forward Fold 
IN: Halfway lift
EX: Chaturanga

Flow 2 15-20 minutes
IN: Dog Split 
EX: Low Lunge
IN: High Lunge 
EX: Power Lunge
IN: High Lunge 
EX: Warrior 2
IN: Reverse Warrior 
EX: Extended Side Angle
IN: Reverse Warrior 
EX: Low Lunge
IN: Plank 
EX: Chaturanga

 
Flow 3 15-20 minutes
IN: Dog Split 
EX: Step Forward
IN: Warrior 1 
EX: Humble Warrior
IN: Low Lunge Twist 
EX: Standing Split
IN: Chair Pose 
EX: Revolved Chair
IN: Chair 
EX: Forward Fold 
IN: Halfway Lift 
EX: Plank > Chaturanga

Final Relaxation (5min)
